{"lc": 1, "type": "constructor", "id": ["langchain", "schema", "document", "Document"], "kwargs": {"metadata": {"doc_id": "428828aa-2967-411f-863a-7b36ba5c44a3", "source": "NexaCorp Policy Handbook v5.2", "part": "3. Human Resources Policies", "section": "3.6 Learning & Development", "subsection": "3.6.4 External Development Programmes", "raw_content": "NexaCorp supports employee participation in external professional development through the following programmes: Annual Learning Stipend: $2,500 per FTE per calendar year for external courses, certifications, conferences, professional memberships, or approved books/subscriptions. Reimbursed via expense claim with receipts. Tuition Assistance: Up to $10,000 per year for degree or graduate programmes directly relevant to the employee's role or career path. Requires 2-year service commitment post-completion; pro-rated clawback if employment ends within the commitment period. Conference Speaker Programme: Employees selected to present at industry conferences receive full expenses coverage and 2 days paid preparation leave. NexaFellow Programme: A 12-month intensive leadership development cohort for high-potential Grade 7\u20138 employees, including executive mentoring, an action-learning project, and an international rotation. Technical Certification Reimbursement: 100% reimbursement of exam fees for approved technical certifications (AWS, GCP, Azure, CISSP, PMP, CFA, etc.) up to 3 certifications per year.", "type": "text", "text": "Part: 3. Human Resources Policies\n            Section: 3.6 Learning & Development\n            Subsection: 3.6.4 External Development Programmes\n            NexaCorp supports employee participation in external professional development through the following programmes: Annual Learning Stipend: $2,500 per FTE per calendar year for external courses, certifications, conferences, professional memberships, or approved books/subscriptions. Reimbursed via expense claim with receipts. Tuition Assistance: Up to $10,000 per year for degree or graduate programmes directly relevant to the employee's role or career path. Requires 2-year service commitment post-completion; pro-rated clawback if employment ends within the commitment period. Conference Speaker Programme: Employees selected to present at industry conferences receive full expenses coverage and 2 days paid preparation leave. NexaFellow Programme: A 12-month intensive leadership development cohort for high-potential Grade 7\u20138 employees, including executive mentoring, an action-learning project, and an international rotation. Technical Certification Reimbursement: 100% reimbursement of exam fees for approved technical certifications (AWS, GCP, Azure, CISSP, PMP, CFA, etc.) up to 3 certifications per year."}, "page_content": "Part: 3. Human Resources Policies\n            Section: 3.6 Learning & Development\n            Subsection: 3.6.4 External Development Programmes", "type": "Document"}}